<TITLE> Gen Masud ready for Canberra job </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Oct 07 (bdnews24.com)Lt General Masud Uddin Chowdhury, a former PSO at Armed Forces Division, will fly to Australia on Oct 26 to take up his new assignment as Bangladesh high commissioner. "Everything is fine. I am leaving for Australia on the 26th ( of October)," Gen Masud told bdnews24.com Tuesday at foreign ministry. Lt General Masud, who was believed to have played an important role during the promulgation of the state of emergency on January 11 last year, held key army posts during the tenure of the military-installed interim government of Fakhruddin Ahmed. Gen Masud was made chief coordinator of the corruption-busting task forces after the declaration of the state of emergency. The general was made commandant of the National Defence College on June 2 before he was transferred to the foreign ministry on June 8 for possible appointment as an ambassador. Gen Masud met foreign secretary Md Touhid Hossain on June 10 and joined the foreign ministry. He was appointed high commissioner to Australia on Sept 2. Born on June 30, 1954 in Feni, Masud was commissioned in the Bangladesh Army on May 1, 1975. b
